{"article_id":"ap4o2hHZp01OeWJV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Hillary Clinton Asks State Dept . To Release Her Emails To The Public","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Responding to concerns over her use of a personal email account","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"to conduct official business while in office ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton says","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"she wants the public to have access to her emails .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"The State Department says","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"it will review messages for possible release .","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"The issue rose to importance earlier this week ,","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"after it was revealed that during her entire tenure at the State Department , Clinton used a personal email account","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"- a move","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that had kept the emails out of the government 's control","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"and circumvented archival practices .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Those practices have become much more stringent in recent years .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"In January , Clinton reportedly provided some 55,000 pages of emails to the State Department ,","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"after her advisers reviewed them .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"On Wednesday , the House Select Committee on Benghazi `` issued a subpoena for all emails","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"related to Libya or Benghazi ''","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"sent from Clinton 's personal account ,","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"as the Two-Way reported .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"Clinton announced her willingness","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"to share the emails with a wider audience late Wednesday ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"saying via Twitter ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"`` I want the public to see my email .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"I asked State to release them . ''","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"`` The State Department will review for public release the emails","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"provided by Secretary Clinton to the Department ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"using a normal process","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that guides such releases .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"We will undertake this review as quickly","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"as possible ;","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"given the sheer volume of the document set ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"this review will take some time","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"to complete . ''","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"As we reported Tuesday ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"it seems that Clinton used a domain","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"named `` clintonemail.com ''","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"to create the email account .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Now The Associated Press says","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"that the server","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that handled the account","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"has been `` traced back to an Internet service","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"registered to her family 's home in Chappaqua , New York . ''","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Earlier this week , The Washington Post reported","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"that the clintonemail.com domain was created on Jan. 13 , 2009","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"- the same day","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Clinton began the confirmation process in the Senate .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":91,"left":0,"right":90,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":90,"left":51,"right":89,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":51,"left":49,"right":50,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":49,"left":47,"right":48,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":47,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":48,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":50,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":89,"left":58,"right":88,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":